  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a significant portion of which has already been restitutioned. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the crime and legal precedents for first-time non-violent white-collar offenses. Taking into account the remorse shown and the partial repayment, a sentence of 6 months is sufficient for punitive and deterrent purposes without causing unnecessary hardship.",
  "verdict": 6
}
